BedFlow AI portfolio platform

Current feature set:
    Model-scored discharge queue, three XGBoost predictions, readiness
    checklist, role-owned tasks, agentic review, authenticated human decisions,
    FHIR-shaped export, capacity what-if simulator, system observability,
    CI/security packaging, and persistent JSON volume support.

Persistence:
    Local default: database/
    Railway/Docker: BEDFLOW_DATA_DIR=/data with a volume mounted at /data
    Keep one application replica when using JSON storage.

Run locally:
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    python app.py

Validation:
    24 automated tests plus the full backend smoke test.

Remaining priorities:
    Model calibration and patient-group validation, formal SHAP explanations,
    screenshots/demo video/GitHub Pages, and optional stronger real-world data.

See README.md, UPGRADE_SUMMARY.md, CHANGELOG.md, and
 docs/PERSISTENT_JSON_STORAGE.md.
